<subSubSection id="C358655E86026B24FAF78A63F81FF96D" pageId="16" pageNumber="79" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586026B24FAF78A63F81FF96D" blockId="16.[1276,2257,1420,1782]" pageId="16" pageNumber="79">
Remarks. As Knight 
<emphasis id="B936EAC786026B24F92A8A63F8C6F9A5" box="[1778,1884,1559,1598]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="79">et al.</emphasis>
(1960) suggested, Carboniferous 
<emphasis id="B936EAC786026B24F9CA8A31F817F9F7" box="[1554,1933,1605,1644]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="79">Ruedemanniaappears</emphasis>
to converge in various characters on 
<emphasis id="B936EAC786026B24F9498A07F8D3F901" box="[1681,1865,1651,1690]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686026B24F9498A07F8DEF901" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1883" box="[1681,1860,1651,1690]" class="Gastropoda" family="Gosseletinidae" genus="Worthenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="16" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Worthenia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In this investigation, specimens possessing conspicuous collabral cords are tentatively referred to 
<emphasis id="B936EAC786026B24F94B8ABBF81FF96D" box="[1683,1925,1743,1782]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686026B24F94B8ABBF81AF96D" authorityName="Foerste" authorityYear="1914" box="[1683,1920,1743,1782]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lophospiridae" genus="Ruedemannia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Murchisoniina" pageId="16" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Ruedemannia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
